data.mission: Consolidate and synthesize recent cognitive work, research findings, and insights into a comprehensive knowledge report. Review accumulated thoughts, agent findings, and memory patterns to identify key themes, connections, and knowledge gaps.

Perform a targeted, comprehensive literature and resource search across the specified mathematical domains (algebra, calculus, geometry, probability, statistics, discrete math, and mathematical modeling). For each domain, collect seminal papers, canonical textbooks, recent survey articles, key theorems, representative worked examples (with references to proofs), and any publicly available datasets or simulation examples; produce an annotated bibliography with direct links and short notes on why each item is important.

Define a fixed output schema (e.g., outputs/results.json fields + figure spec), implement a single deterministic entrypoint (seeded RNG, pinned versions), and document the determinism contract in /outputs/eval_loop.md.

Add a minimal Python script (e.g., scripts/run_pipeline.py) that writes /outputs/run_stamp.json and /outputs/run.log, then add tests/test_artifacts.py asserting files exist and JSON schema keys are present; run pytest and store console output in /outputs/test.log.
